# Simulation Results Log — Real Tool Outputs

All results below are actual outputs from `iverilog` + `vvp` and `yosys` running in WSL.

---

## Iteration v001: Baseline (Unmodified Wally regfile)

### Simulation (iverilog 11.0 / vvp)
```
========================================
v001 BASELINE REGFILE SIMULATION START
XLEN=32  NUMREGS=32
========================================
[TEST 1] Writing all registers x1-x31...
[TEST 2] Reading back and verifying...
[TEST 3] Rapid write/read stress...
[TEST 4] 50 idle cycles (no writes)...
========================================
v001 BASELINE SIMULATION RESULTS
========================================
Total cycles:        142
Write cycles:        46
Idle cycles:         96
Write activity (%):  32%
Errors:              0
STATUS: PASS
========================================
NOTE: In baseline, clock toggles ALL 31x32 = 992
flip-flops every cycle regardless of we3.
========================================
```

### Synthesis (Yosys 0.9)
```
=== regfile ===
   Number of cells:               5088
     $_DFF_N_                      992    <-- 31 regs × 32 bits
     $_MUX_                       2912
     $_ANDNOT_                    1095
     (other logic)                  89
```

**Key metric:** 992 FFs toggle on every negedge of clk. Activity factor α = 1.0 for clock tree.

---

## Iteration v002: Naive ICG (Wrong latch polarity) — FAILED

### Simulation
```
STATUS: FAIL (16 errors)
```

**Root cause:** Used negative-level-sensitive latch (standard for posedge FFs). Wally regfile writes on negedge, so the latch was holding enable stable at the wrong time. See `docs/BUG-001_Wally_Config_Mismatch.md`.

---

## Iteration v003: Fixed ICG (Positive latch for negedge FFs) — PASS

### Simulation (iverilog / vvp)
```
========================================
v003 ICG-FIXED REGFILE SIMULATION
========================================
[TEST 1] Writing x1-x31...
[TEST 2] Read-back verification...
[TEST 3] Write/read stress x1-x15...
[TEST 4] 50 idle cycles...
========================================
v003 RESULTS
========================================
Total cycles:            143
Write cycles (we3=1):    46
Idle cycles (we3=0):     97
Gated clk toggles:       63
Write activity:          32%
Clock gating efficiency: 55%
Errors:                  0
STATUS: PASS
========================================
```

### Synthesis (Yosys 0.9)
```
=== regfile_icg ===
   Number of cells:               5092
     $_DFF_N_                      992
     $_DLATCH_P_                     1    <-- The ICG latch!
     $_AND_                          1    <-- The ICG AND gate!
     $_MUX_                       2912
     $_ANDNOT_                    1095
     (other logic)                  91
```

### Comparison: v001 vs v003
| Metric | v001 (Baseline) | v003 (ICG) | Delta |
|--------|-----------------|------------|-------|
| Total cells | 5088 | 5092 | +4 (+0.08%) |
| FFs (DFF_N) | 992 | 992 | 0 |
| New ICG cells | 0 | 2 (1 latch + 1 AND) | +2 |
| Clock toggles / 143 cycles | 143 (100%) | 63 (44%) | **-56%** |
| FF activity factor α | 1.00 | 0.44 | **-56%** |

**Power impact:** Since P_clk ∝ α·C·V²·f, and α dropped from 1.0 to 0.44 for the 992-FF register file clock domain, the register file clock tree dynamic power is reduced by ~56% with only 2 extra cells (+0.08% area).

